msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/date"
msgid "October 20th, 1941 - Glushkovo, north of Vyazma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/name"
msgid "The Big Prize"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/name_big"
msgid "The Big Prize"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearbridge"
msgid "Excellent! The bridge access seems to have been cleared."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearelevation"
msgid "Excellent job soldiers. This elevated position will no longer be a threat when the weather clears up."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearford"
msgid "Very good. It looks like the fording area has been cleared of hostile troops."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/clearglushkovo"
msgid "A fine display of tactical excellence, soldiers. The village has been neutralized."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/glushkovo"
msgid "Herr Leutnant, scouts are reporting tank movement towards the village of Glushkovo. Unfortunately, in this weather, the Luftwaffe cannot help you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/part2"
msgid "Soldiers! We are not done yet! The enemy still holds the other river bank. It’s imperative we break through and seize all the strategic positions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/part2_2"
msgid "Herr Leutnant, I have been told that we should expect the village of Glushkovo to be heavily defended. The Soviets are holding the line to prevent the encirclement of their troops between Vyazma and Bryansk."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/reinf2"
msgid "Reserves and upgraded equipment are at your disposal Herr Leutnant."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/reinfshow"
msgid "Reinforcements are at your disposal! Use them well. Our reserves are limited."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/start"
msgid "Soldiers! We have orders to clear the road for the attack on Vyazma. But the village ahead keeps us from crossing the Dnieper, and is heavily defended."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/start2"
msgid "We must seize the Dnieper crossings and drive the enemy out of this sector! I expect nothing but the very best from all of you! "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/officer/tank_counter"
msgid "Soviet armored reserves are incoming from the east!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/narrator/soldier/nebelwerfer"
msgid "Friendly casualties located! Those poor guys really ended up in the worst possible place..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/outro_completed"
msgid "After Glushkovo, the attack on Vyazma succeeded and the Germans marched toward Moscow. However, because of the extreme cold and a large-scale Soviet counteroffensive, an attack on the Russian capital was no longer on the cards. Little were they to know they would have to fight over the same place just a few months later."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/outro_failed"
msgid "Not crossing the Dnieper means not taking Vyazma, and many more casualties for Army Group Centre. This mission result means the northern half of the attack on Vyazma is missing, delaying the end of the encirclement by 4 weeks and stopping the German offensive when it matters most."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1941_10_glushkovo/place"
msgid "3rd Panzer Group, Army Group Centre."
msgstr ""

